The paper deals with the problem of on-line matching on bipartite graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper presents a new approach called lazy matching, which is a modification of the classical on-line matching algorithm. The paper uses techniques from graph theory, optimization, and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper also uses techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT), which are also possible sub-categories.
